    "id": "subarray-sum-equals-k",
    "title": "Subarray Sum Equals K",
    "leetcode_url": "https://leetcode.com/problems/subarray-sum-equals-k/",
    "difficulty": "medium",
    "patterns": ["prefix-sum", "hash-map"],
    "topics": ["arrays", "prefix-sum", "hash-table"],
    "frequency_tags": ["faang-common"],
    "has_walkthrough": true,
    "approaches": [
      {
        "name": "Brute Force",
        "time": "O(n²)",
        "space": "O(1)",
        "code": "def subarray_sum(nums, k):\n    count = 0\n    for i in range(len(nums)):\n        s = 0\n        for j in range(i, len(nums)):\n            s += nums[j]\n            if s == k:\n                count += 1\n    return count",
        "explanation": "Try every starting index, sum forward, check each running total. Correct but quadratic."
      },
      {
        "name": "Prefix Sum + Hash Map",
        "time": "O(n)",
        "space": "O(n)",
        "code": "def subarray_sum(nums, k):\n    count = 0\n    prefix = 0\n    seen = {0: 1}  # prefix sum -> count\n    for x in nums:\n        prefix += x\n        if prefix - k in seen:\n            count += seen[prefix - k]\n        seen[prefix] = seen.get(prefix, 0) + 1\n    return count",
        "explanation": "Maintain a running prefix sum. For each position, ask: 'have I seen a prefix sum equal to (current_prefix - k)?' If yes, that means a subarray ending here sums to k. Hash map gives O(1) lookup."
      }
    ]
